<p>The XML for an individual article can be downloaded directly from that article's Web page using the "Download Article XML" link in the sidebar.</p>

<a id="socialBookmarkLinks" name="socialBookmarkLinks"></a>
<h2>Share This Article</h2>
<p>The 'bookmarklet' icons in the right-hand column of every article allow users to save and share links to articles via a number of popular <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_bookmarking" title="Wikipedia | Social bookmarking">"social bookmarking"</a> services such as <a href="http://www.stumbleupon.com" title="Stumble Upon">Stumble Upon</a>, <a href="http://www.facebook.com">Facebook</a>, <a href="http://www.connotea.org/" title="Connotea">Connotea</a>, <a href="http://www.citeulike.org/" title="CiteULike">CiteULike</a>, and <a href="http://digg.com/" title="digg">digg</a>.</p>

<a id="relatedArticles" name="relatedArticles"></a>
<h2>Related Content</h2>
<p>The "Related Content" tab on each article provides links (and information) to additional content which may be related to this article. Among the sources listed, are links to blog posts citing each article; links to other articles or topic categories; links to automated searches on the web; and links to social bookmarking activity. </p>

<h3>Related Articles</h3>
<p>Provides links to:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Related Articles: Links to articles from the same journal that were published together in relation to each other.</li>
	<li>Related Subject Categories: Access to articles that share the same assigned topics.</li>
	<li>Related Articles on the Web: Articles related to the article in <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/" title="PubMed">PubMed</a> and <a href="http://scholar.google.com/" title="Google Scholar">Google Scholar</a>.*</li>
	<li>"Bookmarked in":  Bookmarks to the article in social bookmarking sites such as <a href="http://www.connotea.org/" title="Connotea">Connotea</a> and <a href="http://www.citeulike.org/" title="CiteULike">CiteULike</a>.*</li>
</ul>

<a id="relatedBlogPosts" name="relatedBlogPosts"></a>
<h3>Related Blog Posts</h3>
<p>Provides links to blog posts citing each article via a number of blog aggregation services: <a href="http://www.bloglines.com/" title="Bloglines">Bloglines</a>, <a href="http://www.postgenomic.com/" title="Postgenomic">Postgenomic</a> and <a href="http://blogs.nature.com/" title="Nature Blogs">Nature Blogs</a>.* A link is also provided to blog posts that have linked to the article via a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trackback" title="Wikipedia | Trackback">trackback</a>.</p>
<p>*<em>Please note that the above information is automatically generated via information supplied by each service. PLoS is not responsible (nor able to correct) any errors which originate with the third party concerned.</em></p>

